the phone for 6 months.

762
00:55:01,987 --> 00:55:04,285
When I knew it was
inside the house...

763
00:55:04,356 --> 00:55:09,851
<i>I couldn't think of any</i>
<i>other number to call.</i>
<i>I panicked.</i>

764
00:55:09,928 --> 00:55:12,123
<i>Thank you for coming,</i>
<i>Father.</i>

765
00:55:12,197 --> 00:55:14,791
You're welcome, Ray.

766
00:55:14,866 --> 00:55:18,734
I worked so long that night.

767
00:55:18,804 --> 00:55:21,796
I've never fallen asleep
driving before...

768
00:55:21,873 --> 00:55:23,238
never since.

769
00:55:23,308 --> 00:55:24,468
Don't.

770
00:55:24,543 --> 00:55:26,534
<i>Most of the ride home,</i>

771
00:55:26,611 --> 00:55:30,547
<i>there wasn't a car in sight</i>
<i>in either direction.</i>

772
00:55:30,615 --> 00:55:33,379
<i>If l'd have</i>
<i>fallen asleep then,</i>

773
00:55:33,452 --> 00:55:37,388
<i>I would have ended up in</i>
<i>a ditch with a headache.</i>

774
00:55:37,456 --> 00:55:41,051
<i>And it had to be at that</i>
<i>right moment</i> --

775
00:55:41,126 --> 00:55:45,995
<i>that 10, 15 seconds when</i>
<i>I passed her walking.</i>

776
00:55:46,064 --> 00:55:49,659
It was like
it was meant to be.

777
00:55:58,143 --> 00:56:00,441
I guess if this is
the end of the world,

778
00:56:00,512 --> 00:56:03,276
